[3.1, "o", "\u001b[2J\u001b[HGNU Emacs 30.2  world-cup.md  Markdown  Git:main  Zeta:pair idle\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# World Cup history\r\n\r\nThe tournament started in 1930 and became the most watched sports event on earth.\r\n\r\n* Brazil gave the World Cup its mythology: Pele in 1958, Garrincha in 1962, and\r\n* a gold-shirted style that made skill feel like destiny. Argentina answered with\r\n* Maradona and Messi; France with Zidane and Mbappe; Germany and Italy with machines\r\n* built for pressure. Marta turned the same stage into a global argument for the women's game.\r\n\r\nZeta:\r\n  Replaced selected lines 5..6. No other paragraph was touched.\r\n\r\nThe economics and politics around the event deserve their own section.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nPrecise scoped editing: selected passage rewritten, nearby paragraphs untouched."]
